      "National Power is the ability of a nation to influence the behavior of other nations in accordance with its own will. It is the currency of International Politics — states use power to achieve their objectives and protect their national interests. Hans Morgenthau defined national power as \"man's control over the minds and actions of other men.\" Mahendra Kumar describes it as \"the ability of a nation to fulfill its national goals.\" National power is multidimensional, encompassing military strength, economic capacity, diplomatic influence, and soft power. Understanding national power is essential for analyzing the dynamics of international relations, including alliance formation, conflict, and cooperation.",
